<div id="secondslide" class="nivo-html-caption">
        <div class="banner_caption">
        <img src="images/background/bridge.jpg" class="banner_caption_img" />
       		<div class="caption_box">
          		<div class="left_caption_box">
                    <div class="header_black">Objectives of Project</div>
                    	<div class="content_black">
                        The Akwamu Hills Community Forest Project is a biodiversity sustenance activity with the following objectives among others:
<ol>
<li>Conserve the Akwamu community forest to enhance the ecological integrity and the biological diversity of the Akwamu portion of the Volta basin.</li>
<li>Secure and protect the habitat of the globally threatened White-necked Picathartes, <em><strong>Picathartes gymnocephalus</strong></em> within the community forest;</li>
<li>Promote the biodiversity of the Akwamu Traditional Area with a well conceived interpretative centre;</li>
<li>Develop and implement responsible eco-tourism in the area to create jobs and enhance the economic status of the local communities.</li>
<li>Support local communities in attaining improved economic wellbeing through direct and indirect participation in the ecotourism and related activities.</li>
<li>Promote the museum of history and culture at Akwamufie, to enhance the profile of the Akwamu Traditional Area</li>
</ol>
