<div id="responslide" class="nivo-html-caption">
        <div class="banner_caption">
        <img src="images/background/forest_bg_banner.jpg" class="banner_caption_img" />
       		<div class="caption_box">
          		<div class="left_caption_box">
                    <div class="header_black">Responsible Tourism</div>
                    	<div class="content_forest">
                        The Akwamu Hills Community Forest Project is a biodiversity sustenance activity with the following objectives among others:
<ol>
<li>Extending the 'product offer' of The Royal Senchi, extending the 'product offer' of the area and creating self sustaining 'business' in it's own right;</li>
<li>Conserving the fauna and flora of the partially, degraded 3,000ha site</li>
<li>Preserving the rights of the local population - by limiting the scale of the agreed boundaries of the site so that existing individual constructions and agricultural activities are not interfered with to any great degree;</li>
<li>Enhancing the collective livelihoods of the communities Akwamu Traditional Area, accelerating poverty alleviation pace and influencing pro-poor thinking into local economic development;</li>
<li>Creating a 'shared value model' of integrated sustainable development that is; socially, economically and environmentally responsible, makes business sense, and that like-minded entrepreneurs and/or Government can replicate across Ghana.</li>
</ol>
